			<ns0:name>mseaborn@chromium.org</ns0:name><ns0:uri>/u/mseaborn@chromium.org/</ns0:uri></ns0:author><ns0:content type="html">Currently the GDB debug stub in sel_ldr always expects to get an RSP connection by listening on a TCP port.  This means that debug stub tests cannot be run concurrently and so have to go in large_tests.

We should extend sel_ldr with an option to inherit a file descriptor to use as an RSP connection.  This will allow debug stub tests to run concurrently.

This will also lay the groundwork for improving Chromium integration.  Currently the NaCl process binds the TCP socket, but this doesn't work inside the Chrome sandbox.  We will want the browser process to bind the TCP socket instead.</ns0:content><ns0:updated>2012-10-29T21:49:15.000Z</ns0:updated><ns0:published>2012-08-29T23:40:04.000Z</ns0:published><ns2:status>WontFix</ns2:status><ns2:owner>
			<ns2:uri>/u/mseaborn@chromium.org/</ns2:uri><ns2:username>mseaborn@chromium.org</ns2:username></ns2:owner><ns2:cc>
